[[File:Fredrik Idestam.png|thumb|175px|Fredrik Idestam]] '''Knut Fredrik Idestam''' (28 October 1838, Tyrväntö, [[Grand Duchy of Finland]] – 8 April 1916, [[Helsinki]], [[Grand Duchy of Finland]]) was a [[Finland|Finnish]] [[Mining engineering|mining engineer]] and [[Businessperson|businessman]], best known as a founder of [[Nokia]].
In May 1865, Idestam obtained a permit to construct a groundwood [[paper mill]] at [[Tampere]], [[Finland]]. The mill began operations in 1866. In 1871, Idestam and [[Leo Mechelin]] founded [[Nokia|Nokia Ltd.]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.tn/books?id=HugmyrqibtwC&pg=PA271&dq=leo+mechelin+and+nokia&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwit75W7ydbVAhXGWBQKHe7YDoYQ6AEIKzAB#v=onepage&q=leo%20mechelin%20and%20nokia&f=false|title=Wireless Horizon: Strategy and Competition in the Worldwide Mobile Marketplace|last=Steinbock|first=Dan|date=2003|publisher=AMACOM Div American Mgmt Assn|isbn=9780814407141|language=en}}</ref> and moved the company's operations to the city of [[Nokia, Finland]].
He was buried in the [[Hietaniemi Cemetery]] in Helsinki.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.helsinginseurakunnat.fi/material/attachments/hautausmaat/hietaniemi/w8GZkM0y7/Hietaniemen_merkittavia_vainajia.pdf|title=Hietaniemen hautausmaa – merkittäviä vainajia|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Helsingin seurakuntayhtymä|access-date=27 August 2016}}</ref>
