{{Infobox Officeholder |name = Paweł Tanajno |image = Paweł Tanajno (cropped).jpg |imagesize = 180px |caption = 2015 |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1975|12|19}} |birth_place = [[Warsaw]], [[Polish People's Republic|Poland]] |death_date = |death_place = |alma_mater = [[Nicolaus Copernicus University in Toruń]] (uncertain) }}
'''Paweł Jan Tanajno''' (born December 19, 1975) is a Polish entrepreneur and politician.
He studied Law at [[Nicolaus Copernicus University in Toruń]] and holds a degree in Marketing. From 1995 to 2004 he ran a computer company Sferis. He was also a member of foundations and a member of board of three other companies. He works as internet marketing specialist.<ref>{{cite web|title=Paweł Tanajno|url=https://mamprawowiedziec.pl/strona/polityk/40656_pawel_tanajno/informacje|publisher=MamPrawoWiedzieć.pl|accessdate=12 December 2017}}</ref>
From 2002 to 2003 Tanajno was a member of [[Civic Platform]]. He collaborated with [[Palikot's Movement]] but ended it due to financial inconsistencies in the party. He became a member of [[Direct Democracy (Poland)|Direct Democracy]] in 2012 and served as party's spokesperson.
Tanajno was DB's candidate in [[Polish presidential election, 2015|May 2015 presidential election]]. He gained 29 785 votes (0,2% overall) which placed him at last eleventh position. He unsuccessfully ran for member of Sejm from [[Kukiz'15]] list in October 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sejm election 2015 results|url=http://parlament2015.pkw.gov.pl/349_Wyniki_Sejm/0/0/26|publisher=National Electoral Commission|accessdate=12 December 2017|language=pl}}</ref>
